stylometry: A sensitivity analysis is used to determine the importance of effect a variable has on an equation. Based upon how changing of that variable affects the result of the equation, one may determine it's sensitivity. It is important because it can help a manager make business decisions by ranking the importance of difference decisons. SolverTable provides an array of solutions from the sensitvity analysis that allows the manager to make decisons (since these are the reuslts of the sensitivity analysis). SolverTable is an Add-In that takes the contraints used for the chaning cells and provides results based on the changes of that cell in the intervals one had specified in solver. From these results. one can determine whether or not the variable of the changing cell had an effective impact on the result of the formula.
